		{
			dependencies: ["1F872E31D37B2985"]
			description: [
				"Like getting iron, copper is found in copper veins. Use EMI to check out which ones exist. Unlike in vanilla Minecraft, you'll need a lot of copper to progress through the steam age, because you'll need to make bronze."
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"If you don't like the new texture, just go into the modpack folder, go to kubejs -> assets -> minecraft -> textures -> item and remove the copper ingot texture."
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"Credit to HBM's Nuclear Tech for the texture!"
			]
			id: "72D7B1298C6F67D8"
			subtitle: "Now with a texture makeover!"
			tasks: [{
				count: 8L
				id: "77D8D47CD3C99928"
				item: "minecraft:copper_ingot"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "Copper"
			x: 8.0d
			y: -2.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["1F872E31D37B2985"]
			description: [
				"Get some tin! Like copper and iron, you get this from tin veins, like &7cassiterite&r, &7cassiterite sand&r or &4garnet tin&r."
				"You'll need this for bronze, but you'll need it less than &6copper&r. However, you'll need it for cables in Low Voltage."
